==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Campion
<hw>Cam"pi*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. L.
<ets>campus</ets> field.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant of the
Pink family (<spn>Cucubalus bacciferus</spn>), bearing berries regarded
as poisonous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bladder campion</b></col>, <cd>a plant of the Pink family
(<spn>Cucubalus Behen</spn> or <spn>Silene inflata</spn>), having a much
inflated calyx. See <er>Behen</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Rose
campion</b></col>, <cd>a garden plant (<spn>Lychnis coronaria</spn>)
with handsome crimson flowers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>campmate</ent>⟦br⟧
